comments: I mainly cut the words in two. For two of them the ending bum brought to mind the assosiation of something round and then it was easier to remember which one of the two bigger rounder objectics had 'de' or 'di' sound in it. Then i could recall that the word that started with 'sta' was the vase looking one so i connected the vase and the one that stated with 'sna' together and when i was asked to pick a photo i would have to look at the second letter if the third letter was an 'a'. The word that ended with 'gums' was for a picture that looked like something i might find in a dentists office so i connected the two. Then 'snivoms' i just started remembering after a while without a connection to the others. Then although i dont remember the word there was another one that had an 'e' in it and its photo was in the far left. So whenever i saw an 'e' but no 'bum' i picked that. I believe there was another word and although i remember the picture i cannot remember anything besides the fact that in had an 'i' as the third letter. So when it was none of the above with an 'i' third letter i picked that.
